observations.recommendation:
We reiterated our recommendations that the Municipal Mayor:
• require the Appraisal and Disposal Committee to finish the appraisal, inspection and disposal of these unserviceable properties;
• cause the immediate disposal of the unserviceable properties in order to maximize any realizable value from their disposal by sale and the derecognition of the same for the fair presentation of the financial statements pursuant to Paragraph 82 of IPSAS 17;
• require the Accounting Office to prepare the necessary adjusting entries after the disposal; and
• ensure that the disposal of property either thru public bidding or negotiated sale is properly documented and duly authorized.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
• direct the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to refrain from procuring materials, supplies and equipment through cash advances;
• require the Municipal Accountant to record the purchases of supplies/inventories initially under the appropriate asset account, and recognize the expense account once the inventories are consumed/distributed in accordance with IPSAS 12;
• instruct the Bids and Awards Committee to adhere to the procurement procedures provided in GPPB Circular No. 01-2020 and strictly implement the use of the alternative methods of procurement provided in RA No. 9184; and
• ensure that the granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances is in accordance with COA Circular No. 97-002.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
• require the Appraisal and Disposal Committee to finish the appraisal, inspection and disposal of these unserviceable properties;
• require the Appraisal and Disposal Committee to submit to the Audit Team the required Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) with their technical description together with its supporting documents for the evaluation of unserviceable properties;
• cause the immediate disposal of the unserviceable properties in order to maximize any realizable value from their disposal by sale and the derecognition of the same for the fair presentation of the financial statements;
• require the Accounting Office to prepare the necessary adjusting entries after the disposal; and
• ensure that the disposal of property either thru public bidding or negotiated sale is properly documented and duly authorized.
